<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="137" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="8.[1384,2593,1828,2926]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1386,1737,2621,2650]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Near Threatened on The IUCN Red List (under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nehring" authorityYear="1898" box="[1388,1519,2656,2689]" class="Mammalia" family="Spalacidae" genus="Spalax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="8" pageNumber="138" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="graecus">S. graecus</taxonomicName>
). Additional careful assessment of the Oltenia Blind Mole-rat separate from the Bukovina Blind Mole-rat (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nehring" authorityYear="1898" box="[1815,1944,2699,2728]" class="Mammalia" family="Spalacidae" genus="Spalax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="graecus">S. graecus</taxonomicName>
) and Mehely’s Blind Mole-rat (S. antiquus) is needed. The Oltenia Blind Mole-rat has not been recorded in 30 years and appears to be extremely rare or extinct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
